This being the 200th ^*BDeal of the Week^*N made us feel a little nostalgic so we decided to go back all the way to the birth of contract bridge for this week's deal. This week's deal was played by ^*BHarold S. Vanderbilt^*N who defined the rules and scoring of contract bridge in 1925. Vanderbilt was also one of the best bridge players in the world for many years.

This deal was reported in the very first issue of ^*BThe Bridge World^*N magazine (October 1929) in a feature appropriately named ^*BThe Hand of the Month^*N. This deal is presented as a declarer play problem. The deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.
